    <thetext>Description of problem:
The default font in Gnome 3.x is Cantarell. This font doesn&apos;t seem to support hinting at all. You can see the difference if you compare it to e.g. the liberation fonts.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
abattis-cantarell-fonts-0.0.16-2.fc22.noarch
0.0.16-3.fc23

How reproducible:
always

Steps to Reproduce:
1. open gnome-tweak-tool
2. set hinting to &quot;Medium&quot; or &quot;Full&quot;
3. look at the font face

Actual results:
Font doesn&apos;t seem to do any hinting at all.

Expected results:
Font should look nice and clean with hinting enabled, just as e.g. Liberation Sans does.

Additional info:
Bug reports against Cantarell:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1035486
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1062903</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
